body.name: HDHNBA Computer Chair Mesh Ergonomic Office Chair Home Office Lumbar Support Padded Flip-up Armrest Swivel Desk Chair,Grey
features: [Ergonomic Design] - Contoured frame along the spine provides stable back support. The elasticity of the mesh improves back comfort while dissipating excess heat.

[Flip Armrests] - We designed this table and chair with flip up armrests to maximise space saving, so that when you don't need to use it, you can better store the chair to free up more space for other activities.

[Soft and wearable cushion]: The cushion of this office chair is made of new thick memory foam. The saddle shape contours to the hips and legs, increasing the area of the cushion and further distributing pressure from sitting.

[Smooth and quiet movement]The swivel office chair is equipped with 360-degree rotatable casters for easy movement. The quiet wheels roll smoothly and do no harm to your floors, it can move easily and smoothly on tiles, wooden floors, carpets and other floors, allowing you to enjoy a safe and worry-free glide.

EASY INSTALLATION: Each package contains an instruction manual and the parts needed to assemble the chair. Simply follow the numbers to complete the assembly quickly. If you encounter any problems, our high quality customer service team will solve the problem for you in time

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Movable arm rests are awesome
reviews.reviewText: Movable arm rests allows this chair to fit in a smaller space. My daughter loves it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great chair for the price
reviews.reviewText: I ordered the lime green which is one of my wife's favorite colors and she loves it.As a bigger guy (225lbs) it feels like it flexes a bit when I sit in it but my wife and kids didn't have the same feeling.Everything went together well except one of the arms wasn't quite molded right so I had to modify it a bit so it would come all the way down (reason for being dropped to 4 stars), not enough of an issue to return by all means.Great quality chair overall and I'd recommend it for anyone looking for a unique color.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Nice chair, but definitely not comfortable to sit for long periods of time. You’ll definitely need an extra seat cushion for comfort

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Very firm, but will take your shape
reviews.reviewText: I read some reviews of this chair being uncomfortable, and I see why people feel that way. The cushion is a very firm latex material, so if you are looking for plush, this isn't your chair.It's not like sitting on a concrete bench or aluminum bleacher seat, and the latex slowly conforms around you. The mesh back and arms that fold up are nice features. Otherwise, it is a typical office chair.Are you getting a perfect chair? No. It is more than serviceable though. It is missing those final touches you would see on a higher end chair.Things like plastic flashing around areas where parts were pulled out of the mold, screw holes not in perfect alignment are my main complaints. When you assemble the chair, keep all the bolts loose until they are all installed, and then tighten.With all that said, it is a very sturdy, firm chair that does what a chair should do. I spend 8 plus hours in it daily, and it has shown zero indications of weakness. Being 220lbs at 6' with a boney backside, I can say I really like this chair.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Pop of color and comfort
reviews.reviewText: Chair in the vibrant blue color and I couldn't be happier with my purchase. Not only is the color stunning, but the chair itself is extremely comfortable and has all the features I was looking for in an office chair.One of the best things about this chair is its ergonomic design. As someone who spends long hours at my desk, having a chair that supports my back and promotes good posture is essential. I have noticed a significant improvement in my back pain since using this chair. The mesh material also allows for good air circulation, keeping me cool and comfortable throughout the day.I was pleasantly surprised to find that my 8-year-old son also loves this chair. He often uses it to do his homework or play on the computer, and he appreciates the adjustable height and width. This feature allows the chair to grow with him, making it a long-term investment.Another great aspect of this chair is how easy it was to assemble. It only took me 30 minutes to put together, and I didn't even need the manual.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Comfortable for the price! Super easy to assemble.
reviews.reviewText: This Ergonomic Office Chair came with the screws, an Allen wrench, and an easy to follow instruction diagram. It took me less than 19 minutes to assemble. The back is a breathable nylon mesh which allows airflow and keeps you cool. The seat cushion is also covered in the same breathable nylon mesh. The arm rests rotate up out of the way if you need to roll closer to the desk or push the chair in all the way when not sitting in it. The chair rotates smoothly and easily. It rolls on the wheels with no issues. The height adjustment arm under the seat is a little short or it could be that my arm is a little short. Hahaha! But it works well with no issues. Most of the chair parts are plastic except for the air piston and adjustment arm assembly, which are metal. According to the listing it has been SGS Lab tested to have no loss of serviceability after 120,000 cycles of rotation with 270 lbs. on it. Sounds like it should last a while. It's a fair deal for the price at the time of $59.99. I will update the review down the road if there are any issues. Right now, I am happy with it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Stylish and Chic Office Chair
reviews.reviewText: Overall, this is an attractive office chair that feels sturdyPros:+ Easy to assemble (took around 15 mins for someone alone)+ Bright orange color, looks really nice+ Components feel sturdy+ Easy to clean plastic componentsCons:- Wheels were very difficult to seat properly. Have assembled many, many office chairs and have never had this issue before- One of the threaded inserts for one of the armrests had a defect, making it impossible to get the bolt fully screwed in. The other side went in very smoothly, so the contrast was stark- Back mesh has give, but the back itself is quite rigid. Would not be a comfortable chair for people who lean back by default (poor lumbar support). I perch on chairs, so that isn't a problem for me- White plastic components scuff very easily

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Pretty decent chair for the price!
reviews.reviewText: This chair was easy to assemble, constructed of pretty decent materials. The legs, arms and frames feel solid and sturdy. The top half of the chair does have a little sway on the piston but not a lot. The cushion is thick but compresses easily and may be a bit uncomfortable for bigger individuals. However this is a great deal!
